parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, leading to difficulties in turning off the engine, draining the battery, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the key is difficult to remove from the ignition
the key does not rotate to the off position
the engine does not turn off
the battery drains
and the transmission fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the rear window defogger to malfunction, leading to burning of the wiring and socket, and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The rear window defogger is burning wiring and socket
and the circuit has a 40amp fuse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer gauge can cause the driver to be unable to determine their speed, leading to potential safety issues.
symptoms: The speedometer gauge is difficult to read in cloudy or overcast weather conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and clunking can cause the vehicle to jerk, slip, or hesitate when accelerating, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the transmission clunks or makes a loud noise when shifting
the vehicle struggles to shift into gear
the engine revs high when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure to engage can cause the vehicle to stall or not move when accelerating, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or does not move when accelerating
the vehicle struggles to shift into gear
the engine revs high when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch plate failure can cause the transmission to slip or hesitate when accelerating, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The clutch plate is melted
planetary bearings are destroyed
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when making turns or parking.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fails
the steering wheel binds and is resistant
a clattering noise occurs
the vehicle spins out of control
the airbags fail to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The ignition switch does not completely turn off
the key cannot be removed from the ignition
the vehicle stalls or loses power.
